               <head>John‏ Climacus, Scala paradisi; Sermons. A) (fols 1–27) Mainz Charterhouse, s. xiv<hi rend="superscript">ex</hi>; B) (fols 28–71) Germany, s. xiv<hi rend="superscript">in</hi>; C) (fols 72–161) Germany, c.1300.</head>
               <physDesc>
                  <p>This description is abbreviated from Daniela Mairhofer, <title>Medieval Manuscripts from the Mainz Charterhouse in the Bodleian Library, Oxford: A Descriptive Catalogue</title> (Oxford, 2018), pp. 925–973. For purposes of scholarly citation, reference to the printed catalogue is requested.</p>
                  <p n="composite">Composite: A) (fols 1–27) || B) (fols 28–71) || C) (fols 72–161)</p>
                  <objectDesc form="codex">
                     <supportDesc material="perg">
                        <support>parchment</support>
                        <extent>i (17th-cent.) + 161 + i (17th-cent.) leaves</extent>
                        <foliation>i, 1–162, in modern (19th-cent.) pencil</foliation>
                        <collation>A) i &amp; ii 10 (fols 1–20) | iii 8-1; B) iv–vi 12 | vii 8; C) viii–xiii 12 | xiv 12-1 | xv 8-1</collation>
                     </supportDesc>
                  </objectDesc>
                  <bindingDesc>
                     <binding calendar="Gregorian" notAfter="1639" notBefore="1637">
                        <p>Brown tanned calf over laminated pulpboard for Abp. Laud, 1637–1639.</p>
                     </binding>
                  </bindingDesc>
               </physDesc>
               <history><provenance when="1638"><persName key="person_54940373" role="fmo">William Laud, 1573–1645</persName>: MS. Laud Misc. 323 consists of three different parts, which were possibly bound together only in the course of the Laudian binding. Ex-libris inscription of Archbishop Laud, dated 1638, at the lower margin of fol. i verso.</provenance>
                  <acquisition when="1639">Given to the Bodleian as part of his third donation, dispatched on 28 June 1639.</acquisition></history>
               <additional>
